  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "GBA save: no magic. Type determined by file size: 512=EEPROM 4Kbit, 8192=EEPROM 64Kbit, 32768=SRAM 256Kbit, 65536=Flash 512Kbit, 131072=Flash 1Mbit. Pokemon RSE: 14 sections x 4096 bytes, each with 128-byte footer (section ID uint16, checksum uint16, save index uint32, section size uint16). Flash chip IDs: 0xBF/0xD4=SST/Sanyo, 0xC2/0x1C=Macronix, 0x1F/0x13=Atmel.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Determine storage type from file size: 512=EEPROM 4K, 8192=EEPROM 64K, 32768=SRAM, 65536=Flash 512K, 131072=Flash 1M",
      "For Pokemon RSE (131072 bytes): read section ID at offset 0x0FF4 (uint16 LE) and checksum at 0x0FF6 of first 4096-byte section",
      "Check for erased Flash byte patterns (0xFF fill) indicating unwritten sectors",
      "Verify save data integrity by computing game-specific checksums (Pokemon: sum of 0xE0 uint32 values per section)"
    ]
  },
